Detailed Description

This class is responsible for parsing command line arguments and validating user inputs.

The Parser class extends the CommandLine class template with InLab10Inputs as the template argument. It provides methods to build input arguments, print input arguments, perform checks on input arguments, and build inputs based on the parsed arguments.

The Parser class extends the CommandLine class template with InLab11Inputs as the template argument. It provides methods to build input arguments, print input arguments, perform checks on input arguments, and build inputs based on the parsed arguments.

The Parser class extends the CommandLine class template with InLab12Inputs as the template argument. It provides methods to build input arguments, print input arguments, perform checks on input arguments, and build inputs based on the parsed arguments.

The Parser class extends the CommandLine class template with OutLab7Inputs as the template argument. It provides methods to build input arguments, print input arguments, perform checks on input arguments, and build inputs based on the parsed arguments.

The Parser class extends the CommandLine class template with OutLab10Inputs as the template argument. It provides methods to build input arguments, print input arguments, perform checks on input arguments, and build inputs based on the parsed arguments.

The Parser class extends the CommandLine class template with OutLab11Inputs as the template argument. It provides methods to build input arguments, print input arguments, perform checks on input arguments, and build inputs based on the parsed arguments.

The Parser class extends the CommandLine class template with OutLab12Inputs as the template argument. It provides methods to build input arguments, print input arguments, perform checks on input arguments, and build inputs based on the parsed arguments.

)
inlineoverrideprotectedvirtual

Builds the input matrices for the MyBLAS library from a JSON file.

This function reads the input JSON file and extracts the coefficient matrix and constants vector. It also validates the dimensions of the input matrices and sets the order of the system. If the verbose mode is enabled, it prints the input matrices.

Parameters
inputsReference to a MyBLAS::InputMatrices object to store the input matrices.
valuesReference to a boost::program_options::variables_map object containing the command line arguments.

Implements CommandLine< OutLab12Inputs >.

122  // read the upper matrix, add it to LU, and subtract identity matrix to remove double counting
123  const auto lower = MyBLAS::Matrix(std::vector<std::vector<long double>>(inputMap["lower"]));
124  const auto upper = MyBLAS::Matrix(std::vector<std::vector<long double>>(inputMap["upper"]));
125 
126  if (lower.getCols() != upper.getCols() || lower.getRows() != upper.getRows()) {
127  std::cerr
128  << "Error: Input lower and upper triangular matrices do not have the same dimensions, aborting.\n";
129  exit(-1);
130  }
131 
132  if (lower.getCols() != upper.getRows()) {
133  std::cerr << "Error: Input matrices not square, aborting.\n";
134  exit(-1);
135  }
136 
137  if (lower.getRows() != inputs.constants.size()) {
138  std::cerr << "Error: Input constants vector not order n, aborting.\n";
139  exit(-1);
140  }
141 
142  // set input order n
143  const auto orderFromInputMatrixDimensions = lower.getRows();
144  if (values["order"].defaulted()) {
145  std::cout << "Reading matrix order (n) from input matrix dimensions: " << orderFromInputMatrixDimensions
146  << "\n";
147  inputs.n = orderFromInputMatrixDimensions;
148  } else { // user provided some value for n, validate against input dimensions
149  const auto orderFromUser = static_cast<size_t>(values["order"].as<long double>());
150  inputs.n = orderFromUser > orderFromInputMatrixDimensions ? orderFromInputMatrixDimensions : orderFromUser;
151  if (orderFromUser > orderFromInputMatrixDimensions) {
152  std::cerr << "Warning: Matrix order (n) is larger than input matrices, defaulting to lower value\n";
153  }
154  }
155 
156  const auto identity = MyBLAS::Matrix<long double>::eye(inputs.n);
157  inputs.LU = lower + upper - identity;
158 
159  // print the matrices since we are in verbose mode.
160  if (!values.count("quiet")) {
161  const auto precision = getCurrentPrecision();
162  printLine();
163  std::cout << "Lower Triangular Matrix (L):\n";
164  printLine();
165  std::cout << std::setprecision(static_cast<int>(precision)) << lower;
166  printLine();
167  std::cout << "Upper Triangular Matrix (U):\n";
168  printLine();
169  std::cout << std::setprecision(static_cast<int>(precision)) << upper;
170  printLine();
171  std::cout << "Constants Vector (b):\n";
172  printLine();
173  std::cout << std::setprecision(static_cast<int>(precision)) << inputs.constants;
174  printLine();
175  printLine();
176  std::cout << "LU Matrix:\n";
177  printLine();
178  std::cout << std::setprecision(static_cast<int>(precision)) << inputs.LU;
179  }
180  }

241  std::cout << "Input coefficients matrix A is diagonally dominant.\n";

246  } else if (!values.count("quiet")) {
247  std::cout << "Input coefficients matrix A is positive definite.\n";
248  }

253  input.methods.insert(MyRelaxationMethod::METHOD_DIRECT_POWER_ITERATION);
254  }

Builds the input matrices for the MyBLAS library from a JSON file.

This function reads the input JSON file and extracts the coefficient matrix and constants vector. It also validates the dimensions of the input matrices and sets the order of the system. If the verbose mode is enabled, it prints the input matrices.

Parameters
inputsReference to a MyBLAS::InputMatrices object to store the input matrices.
valuesReference to a boost::program_options::variables_map object containing the command line arguments.

Implements CommandLine< OutLab12Inputs >.

Builds the input matrices for the MyBLAS library from a JSON file.

This function reads the input JSON file and extracts the coefficient matrix and constants vector. It also validates the dimensions of the input matrices and sets the order of the system. If the verbose mode is enabled, it prints the input matrices.

virtual void CommandLine< OutLab12Inputs >::initialize ( )
inlineprotectedvirtualinherited

Method to initialize the CommandLine object. This method initializes the CommandLine object by printing the compile configurations and precision information, and parsing the command line arguments. If the CommandLine object is already initialized, it does nothing.

319  {
320 
321  if (initialized) {
322  return;
323  }
324 
325  // print the header
326  printHeader(header);
327 
328  initialized = true;
329  boost::program_options::options_description options("Parameters");
330  buildInputArguments(options);
331  options.add(buildGenerics());
332  boost::program_options::store(boost::program_options::parse_command_line(cmdArgs.argc, cmdArgs.argv, options),
333  variablesMap);
334  boost::program_options::notify(variablesMap);
335 
336  // if help, print options and exit
337  if (variablesMap.count("help")) {
338  std::cout << options << "\n";
339  exit(0);
340  }
341 
342  // print compiler information
343  if (!variablesMap.count("quiet")) {
344  printCompileConfigs();
345  // print command line options
346  std::cout << options << "\n";
347  printLine();
348  printPrecisionInformation();
349  }
350 
351  // consume and correct the input arguments
352  performInputArgumentsCheck(variablesMap);
353 
354  if (variablesMap.count("bench")) {
355  // build the profiler now
356  ProfilerHelper::validateOptions(variablesMap);
357  }
358 
359  if (!variablesMap.count("quiet")) {

117  // Create a data map

164  while (isUnfilledVector<long double>(map, "x-points", n)) {

124  const std::string filename = map["input-csv"].as<std::string>();
125  std::cout << "Reading from file: " << filename << std::endl;
126  try {
127  // Create a data map
128  std::map<std::string, std::vector<long double>> dataMap;
129  // Fill data, mapping csv headers (keys) to csv columns (value vectors)

131 
132  // Read column x if provided and update the number of points
133  if (dataMap.count("x")) {
134  std::vector<long double> x_vec_inputs = dataMap["x"];
135  replace(map, "x-points", x_vec_inputs);
136  replace(map, "num-points", static_cast<long double>(dataMap["x"].size()));
137  }
138  // Read column fx if provided
139  if (dataMap.count("f(x)")) {
140  replace(map, "fx-points", dataMap["f(x)"]);

142  } catch (...) {
143  std::cerr << "..failed. Aborting." << std::endl;
144  exit(1);
145  }
146  }

149  while (map["num-points"].empty() || failsNaturalNumberCheck(map["num-points"].as<long double>())) {
150  std::cout << "Enter the number of interpolation points: ";
151  std::cin >> input;
152  try {
153  replace(map, "num-points", asNumber(input));
154  } catch (const std::exception &) {
155  continue;
156  }
157  }

159  // Prompt the user to enter the number of Lagrange interpolation evaluation points until a valid input is
160  // provided

164  try {
165  replace(map, "num-samples", asNumber(input));
166  } catch (const std::exception &) {
167  continue;
168  }
169  }

171  const auto n = static_cast<size_t>(map["num-points"].as<long double>());
172  std::vector<long double> x_vec_inputs = map["x-points"].as<std::vector<long double>>();
173  bool messageShown = false;
174  // Prompt the user to enter the interpolation points until the required number of points is provided
175  while (isUnfilledVector<long double>(map, "x-points", n)) {
176  if (!messageShown) {
177  std::cout << "Enter points for the interval x, sorted, and one at a time: " << std::endl;
178  messageShown = true;
179  }
180  std::cin >> input;
181 
182  // attempting to insert non-increasing or non-unique value!
183  if (!x_vec_inputs.empty() && asNumber(input) <= x_vec_inputs.back()) {
184  std::cerr << "Cannot accept non-increasing values for x, try again.\n";
185  continue;
186  }
187

189  x_vec_inputs.push_back(asNumber(input));
190  replace(map, "x-points", x_vec_inputs);
191  } catch (...) {
192  std::cerr << "That wasn't a number, try again.\n";
193  continue;
194  }
195  }

199  try {
200  std::vector<long double> x = map["x-points"].as<std::vector<long double>>();
201  std::vector<long double> fx_vec_inputs(x.size(), 0.0f);
202  fill_fx(x, fx_vec_inputs);
203  replace(map, "fx-points", fx_vec_inputs);
204  replace(map, "x-points", x);
205  } catch (...) {
206  std::cerr << "Error: Executing external method 'fill_fx' failed. Aborting\n";
207  exit(1);
208  }
209  }
210 
211  std::vector<long double> fx_vec_inputs;
212  messageShown = false;
213  // Prompt the user to enter the f(x) values until the required number of values is provided
214  while (isUnfilledVector<long double>(map, "fx-points", n)) {
215  if (!messageShown) {
216  std::cout << "Enter " << n << " points for f(x) for every x, one at a time: " << std::endl;
217  messageShown = true;
218  }
219  std::cin >> input;
220  try {
221  fx_vec_inputs.push_back(asNumber(input));
222  replace(map, "fx-points", fx_vec_inputs);
223  } catch (...) {
224  std::cerr << "That wasn't a number, try again.\n";
225  continue;
226  }

73  std::cout << std::setw(16) << "x" << std::setw(34) << "f(x)\n" << std::scientific;
74  for (size_t i = 0; i < x.size(); i++) {
75  const auto x_sign = (x[i] >= 0) ? "+" : "";
76  const auto fx_sign = (fx[i] >= 0) ? "+" : "";
77  std::cout << "\t" << x_sign << std::setprecision(static_cast<int>(precision)) << x[i];
78  std::cout << "\t\t\t" << fx_sign << std::setprecision(static_cast<int>(precision)) << fx[i] << std::endl;
79  }
80  CommandLine::printLine();
81  std::cout << "\tnum-points, n: " << n << "\n";
82  std::cout << "\tnum-samples, m: " << m << "\n";
83  if (vm.count("input-csv") && !vm["input-csv"].empty()) {
84  std::cout << "\tinput-csv, i: " << vm["input-csv"].as<std::string>() << "\n";
85  }
86  std::cout << "\toutput-csv, o: " << vm["output-csv"].as<std::string>() << "\n";
87  CommandLine::printLine();
88  }

protectedinherited

A boolean flag to indicate whether the CommandLine object has been initialized.

This flag is set to true when the CommandLine object is initialized, and is used to prevent the object from being initialized more than once.
